/*
;⮞--------------------- SUMMARY -----------------------------------------∙ 
∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙ 
» When the hotkey combination (Shift+w or Shift+s in this case) is pressed, the script sends the respective key (w or s) repeatedly while the key combination is held down. The delay between repetitions is initially set to 30 milliseconds and can be toggled off and on by pressing the hotkey combination multiple times in quick succession.

;∙---------------------- 

• • Line by Line Break Down • • 

period := 30 ; Milliseconds
• This sets the variable period to 30 milliseconds. This variable determines the delay between each repetition when the hotkey is held down.

$+w::
• This defines a hotkey combination "Shift + w". The $ prefix ensures that the hotkey won't trigger itself by sending another key press. The + represents the Shift modifier.

$+s::
• This defines a hotkey combination "Shift + s", similar to the line above.

last := hk, hk := SubStr(A_ThisHotkey, 0)
• This line sets the variable last to the value of hk, then updates hk to the substring of A_ThisHotkey starting from the 0th character. A_ThisHotkey contains the name of the currently executing hotkey.

If (on = period && hk = last) {
• This begins an if statement. It checks if the variable on is equal to period and if hk is equal to last.

SetTimer spam, % on := "Off"
• If the condition in the if statement is true, this line sets a timer named "spam" to turn off ("Off") after the delay specified by on (which is 30 milliseconds initially).

Return
• This ends the if statement.

} Else SetTimer spam, % on := period
• If the condition in the if statement is false, this line sets a timer named "spam" to activate after the delay specified by on, which is then set to period (30 milliseconds).

Spam:
• This label marks the beginning of the section of code that the timer "spam" will execute.

Send % hk
• This line sends the key combination stored in the variable hk.

Return
• This ends the timer subroutine.
∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙=∙ 
;∙---------------------- SUMMARY END -----------------------------------∙ 
*/

period := 30 ; Milliseconds

$+w:: 	 ; (Shift+w)
$+s:: 	 ; (Shift+s)

last := hk, hk := SubStr(A_ThisHotkey, 0)

If (on = period && hk = last) {
    SetTimer spam, % on := "Off"
Return
    } Else SetTimer spam, % on := period

Spam:
    Send % hk
Return





